LAFIA – Nasarawa State government said it has earmarked the sum of N2.23billion from the 2022 budget for the electrification of rural communities across the state. Honourable Daniel Agyeno, the state Commissioner of Finance, Budget and Planning Commission, made the disclosure during the budget breakdown at the Ministry in Lafia, the state capital. According to him, the 2022 budget tagged “Budget of Sustainable Transformation” was based on the collective purpose to sustain the pace of development in the state. Emir Of Borgu Inaugurates Committee On Gani Durbar Festival Gombe: Inuwa Appoints Prof Amuga As Special Adviser On Project… The commissioner also explained that the government also earmarks N2.8bn for the construction of Urban, Rural roads. Agyeno, note that the amount set aside for the construction of the road was captured in the State’s 2022 Budget which was recently signed into law by Governor Abdullahi Sule. He said, “The state government will embark on the construction of some Urban roads in Obi Local Government Area, Karu LGA, Keana LGA, Toto LGA, Keffi LGA, Akwanga LGA, Wamba LGA, Doma LGA and Garaku town in Kokona LGA. “We are also going to construct and rehabilitate some rural roads across the 13 LGAs of the state. The construction of the urban roads would gulp the sum of N700 million while that of the rural roads would gulp the sum of N2.1 billion and these monies were captured the 2022 budget of N110.8 billion tagged Budget of Sustainable Transformation”. Agyeno, however, advised all accounting officers of ministries, departments and agencies in the state to be guided by the appropriation law and ensure that all revenue generated for state government are properly collected and accounted for as his ministry would embark on strict monitoring of their activities.